text: Juana Isidra Fernández (born May 15, 1971) is a road cyclist from the Dominican Republic. She became Dominican Republic national road race and time trial champion in 2014 and Time Trial Champion in 2015. ==Palmarès== ;2014 :1st 20px National Time Trial Championship :1st 20px National Road Race Championship ;2015 :1st 20px National Road Race Championship ;2016 :Puerto Rico Track Cup Conacip ::1st Omnium ::1st Scratch Race ::2nd Keirin ::2nd Sprint ==References== ==External links== * profile at Procyclingstats.com Category:Dominican Republic female cyclists Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:Cyclists at the 2003 Pan American Games Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
